  "dataFlow": "External trigger (GitHub push, Linear webhook, Telegram message, cron, or dashboard form) arrives at FastAPI backend. Webhooks are HMAC-verified before processing. Browser requests are cookie-authenticated via HMAC-signed session tokens. Authenticated build requests call create_session(), which places a BuildSession in the in-memory _sessions dict and atomically persists it to app/logs/sessions/{sid}.json. The run_build() coroutine executes the SDK-only 5-phase pipeline: (1) repo clone into app/workspaces/{sid}/, (2) PITER intent classification + skill injection to build a structured prompt, (3) ClaudeSDKClient generator phase streams output lines appended to session.output_lines, (4) evaluator grades the git diff and emits PASS/FAIL, (5) git commit + push back to origin. All output_lines are simultaneously streamed to the browser over WebSocket /ws/build/{sid} and available via SSE /api/sessions/{sid}/logs. Terminal build events and quality gate results are written fire-and-forget to Supabase (gate_checks table) via supabase_log.py. The autonomy poller independently queries Linear GraphQL every 5 minutes, picks up Urgent/High Todo issues, and calls create_session() for each. Cron triggers in cron-triggers.json are dispatched by cron_loop() to scanner.py (Pi-SEO), pi_seo_monitor.py (health digest), board_meeting.py (minutes), and anthropic_intel_refresh (docs fetch). Scan findings above severity thresholds flow through triage.py to the Linear API and to Telegram. Harness state (.harness/) is read by the MCP server and exposed as structured tools to Claude Desktop; the MCP server never writes to the harness. Marathon watchdog reads harness state every 30 minutes and pushes Telegram escalations when health checks fail. Inbound Telegram messages are polled by marathon_telegram_inbox.py, written as JSON to .harness/telegram-inbox/, drained by the watchdog, and routed to .harness/ideas-from-phone/ or self-heal actions.",
